(a) Distributes nursery stock without
a nursery stock distributor license issued under the Plant Protection
and Plant Pest Act;

(c) Uses any license issued by the department after it has been revoked
or has expired, while the licensee was under suspension, or for purposes other
than those authorized by the act;

(e) Allows any plant declared a nuisance plant as outlined in section
2-10,107 to exist on such person's property or distributes any such plants
or materials capable of harboring plant pests;

(k) Fails to keep and make available for examination by the department
all books, papers, and other information necessary for the enforcement of
the act;
